snippet.title: Passenger trapped in car crash in west Warwick
snippet.content:
PARAMEDICS have just arrived on the scene of a car crash in west Warwick.
Crews were called to the corner of Tooth and Pratten Sts at about 5.10 this afternoon after two cars reportedly collided.
A Queensland Ambulance Service spokeswoman said initial reports suggest at least one person may be entrapped in a vehicle.
Updates to follow.
